title: F1 world reacts to Red Bull drama
text:
TWO years ago, Red Bull was unbeatable in Formula 1. 
Now it could pull out of the sport altogether. 
The team’s relationship with long-time engine supplier Renault has collapsed acrimoniously in what seems set to be Red Bull’s first winless season since 2008. Late October is the deadline for a decision, Red Bull owner Dietrich Mateschitz says. Where will Daniel Ricciardo be in 2016? Ricciardo’s teammate Daniil Kvyat is staying patient. Max Verstappen is “not afraid”. Lewis Hamilton says the entire situation is “odd”. Head of Mercedes, Toto Wolff. 1 of n 
Without an engine confirmed for 2016, it is far from clear whether Red Bull and its Austrian drinks baron owner Dietrich Mateschitz will be back. 
It’s not just fans who are confused about the rapid turnaround. 
Here’s what the F1 world is saying. Other Stories
